# Plan — {{PLAN_TITLE}}

> A **durable plan** (`planning/plans/<slug>.md`) — the persisted output of a planner plan-mode pass, saved
> on approval (VAN-CLIEF §9). This is the **source-of-truth *how*** for one initiative; `roadmap.md` holds
> the *what / when* and `srd.md` the *spec*. `todo.md` does **not** restate this — it carries a thin task
> that **routes here** (`→ plan: planning/plans/<slug>.md` · slice `<handle>`). **One task per slice.**
>
> Status: <draft | approved | building | done>  ·  Created: {{YYYY-MM-DD}}  ·  Supersedes: <plan or —>

## Context
Why this initiative — the problem/need, what prompted it, the intended outcome. (Pull from the
mission-brief / `srd.md` / the `roadmap.md` item this realizes.)

## Design
The approach — the *how*: key decisions and the shape of the change. Name existing code/utilities to
**reuse** (path + symbol). This is the body of the approved plan-mode plan — the detail that used to bloat
`todo.md` lives here instead.

## Slices
> A **large** plan shards across workers — one `### Slice` per worker, each becoming **one** `todo.md` task
> routed to it by handle (slice `<handle>`). A **small** plan is a single slice → one worker.

### Slice: <handle> — <short scope>
- **Goal:** <the outcome>
- **Done-looks-like / Verify-by:** <the verifiable check the worker runs and surfaces — also the `/goal` condition>
- **Context:** <named inputs — files, data, prior decisions to read first>
- **Constraints:** <scope · **Must NOT** include · out-of-bounds>
- **Claims (if any):** <`planning/claims/<id>` minted for any high-stakes assumption this slice rests on — the verifier checks it>

